## importa dados


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
milho <- gsheet2tbl("https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1bq2N19DcZdtax2fQW9OHSGMR0X2__Z9T/edit#gid=1345524759")
```
:::


## Vizualizar


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
milho |> 
  ggplot(aes(method, index))+
  geom_jitter(width = 0.01, color = "black")+
  facet_wrap(~hybrid)+
  stat_summary(fun.data = "mean_cl_boot", color = 'black', size = 0.5, alpha = 0.5)+
  theme_few()+
    labs(x = 'Method',
       y = 'Index')
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula_8_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


## Modelo para análise estatística em parcelas subdivididas

### Variável 1


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
milho <- milho |> 
  mutate(block = as.factor(block))

mix2 <- lmer(sqrt(index) ~ hybrid*method + block + (1|block/hybrid), data = milho) # Modelos Lineares de Efeitos Mistos
 
Anova(mix2)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
Analysis of Deviance Table (Type II Wald chisquare tests)

Response: sqrt(index)
                Chisq Df Pr(>Chisq)   
hybrid        15.3159  5   0.009095 **
method         3.8886  1   0.048615 * 
block          0.0783  3   0.994305   
hybrid:method 13.3812  5   0.020057 * 
---
Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
```
:::
:::


### Testando a premissas


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
check_normality(mix2)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
OK: residuals appear as normally distributed (p = 0.440).
```
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
check_heteroscedasticity(mix2)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
OK: Error variance appears to be homoscedastic (p = 0.970).
```
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
qqnorm(residuals(mix2))
qqline(residuals(mix2))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula_8_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
hist(residuals(mix2))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](Aula_8_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-5-2.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
shapiro.test(residuals(mix2))
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```

	Shapiro-Wilk normality test

data:  residuals(mix2)
W = 0.97643, p-value = 0.44
```
:::
:::

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
                        ~ hybrid | method,
                        type = "response")

medias_milho2 <- emmeans(mix2,
                        ~ method | hybrid,
                        type = "response")

```
